    "title": "Entry-Level Radiologist at Tata Memorial Centre",
    "description": "Tata Memorial Centre, one of India's leading organizations, is hiring a Radiologist for our Srinagar operations. We offer a competitive salary package along with world-class benefits.\n\nAbout Tata Memorial Centre:\nTata Memorial Centre is a leading organization in the Remote sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Administer medications and treatments as prescribed\n• Coordinate with multidisciplinary teams for comprehensive patient management\n• Attend continuing medical education programs and training\n• Maintain accurate clinical documentation in electronic health records\n• Diagnose and treat medical conditions following established protocols\n• Maintain sterile environments and follow infection control protocols\n• Participate in quality improvement initiatives and clinical audits\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• Chartered Accountant (ICAI)\n• 0-1 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Pharmacovigilance\n• Proficiency in Medical Coding\n• Proficiency in Health Informatics\n• Proficiency in Infection Control\n• Proficiency in Medical Terminology\n• Proficiency in Telemedicine\n• Proficiency in Diagnostic Skills\n• Proficiency in HIPAA Compliance\n\nWork Mode: Remote - Work from anywhere in India\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Recognition and rewards programs\n• Meal coupons and food allowance\n• Maternity and paternity leave\n• Mobile and internet reimbursement\n• Provident Fund and Gratuity as per company policy\n• Comprehensive health insurance for self and family\n• Salary Range: 2.5 LPA - 6 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Srinagar, Jammu & Kashmir, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Tata Memorial Centre!",
